# Meeting Recording Panel Redesign (April 2026)

Completed 2026-04-05 (commit `91c0dd8`). Redesigned MeetingNotesFloatingPanel to match updated Figma specs.

**Why:** The panel's layout, button styling, and recording indicator needed to match the refreshed Figma design. The user also wanted a reactive audio waveform instead of the pulsing dot.

**How to apply:** Reference when working on meeting panel code. The panel's structure fundamentally changed.

## Key Structural Changes

- Layout flipped: **tabs on top, content in middle, controls at bottom** (was controls on top)
- Panel width: **383px** (was 400px)
- Expanded height: **299px** fixed (all expanded states)
- Collapsed state: 2-row vertical (info bar + buttons), not a horizontal pill
- Tab segments: equal-width (flex), 34px height, capsule shape
- Content area: explicit `SurfaceDefaultColor` background, 14px corner radius
- Action buttons: full-width tinted capsules (orange 25% pause, blue 25% play, red 25% stop)
- Square utility buttons (X, expand/minimize): 34x34, `ButtonSecondaryBgColor`

## New Components

- `AudioWaveformIndicator.swift` -- 18x18 view, 4 bars reactive to `AudioRecorder.levels` (recording) or 4 static dots (paused)
- New color tokens: `MeetingRecordingColor` (#EF4444), `MeetingPausedColor` (#F97316)
- New icons downloaded from Figma: IconPause, IconPlayCircle, StopCircle, IconExpand45, IconMinimize45

## User Overrides from Figma

- Timer + state text: **keep monospaced** (FontManager.metadata/heading, not Figma's SF Pro Label-5)
- BrailleLoader + shimmer: **stay** for "Generating summary" (not Figma's blue dots)
- No action buttons during summary generation (match Figma)
- Summary tab only visible after wrap-up (fades in on stop)
- Waveform **reactive to actual audio levels** (AudioRecorder.levels, 28 bars sampled down to 4)

## Tab Visibility Rules

- Recording/paused: only Transcript + Notes tabs
- After wrap-up (processing/complete): Summary + Transcript + Notes (Summary fades in)
